<a
    href="https://foreignpolicy.com/category/five-reads/"
    class="department-name">
    <h3 class="department">5 Top Reads</h3></a>
<span
    class="hed-heading"
    href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/06/06/china-united-states-george-floyd-protests/">
    <h1 class="hed">Our Top Weekend Reads</h1>
</span>
<h2 class="dek-heading">China condemns America&#039;s human rights record, the United States is sliding into illiberalism, and workers will be the most vulnerable when businesses reopen.</h2>
<div class="meta-data ">
    <address class="author-list">
    <span class="pre">By</span>
    <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/author/dan-haverty/"
        rel="author"
        class="author">
    Dan Haverty</a></address>
    <span class="separator">|</span>
    <time
    pubdate
    datetime="2020-06-06"
    title="June 6th, 2020"
    class="date-time">
June 6, 2020, 7:00 AM</time>
</div>




				<figure class="figure-image ">
            <span
            style="padding-bottom:66.666666666667%;
        "
                class="image-attachment -ratioscale  horizontal-orientation">
        <img
            data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"
            data-srcset="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?quality=90 1500w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=150,100&amp;quality=90 150w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=550,367&amp;quality=90 550w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=90 768w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=400,267&amp;quality=90 400w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=401,267&amp;quality=90 401w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=800,533&amp;quality=90 800w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=275,183&amp;quality=90 275w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=325,217&amp;quality=90 325w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?resize=600,400&amp;quality=90 600w"
            data-src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?w=800&#038;h=533&#038;quality=90"
            sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"
            src=""
            alt="People gather in the rain outside the White House for a peaceful protest against police brutality."
            style="width:auto;"
            class="image -fit -lazy"
        >
        <noscript>
            <img
                src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/black-lives-matter-washington-dc-united-states-1217662324.jpg?w=800&#038;h=533&#038;quality=90"
                alt="People gather in the rain outside the White House for a peaceful protest against police brutality."
                class="image -fit-3-2">
        </noscript>
        </span>
                    <div class="caption">
            People gather in the rain outside the White House for a peaceful protest against police brutality in Washington on June 4.            <span class="attribution">Sarah Silbiger/Getty Images</span>
        </div>
    </figure>


				
			
			
						
			<div class="post-content-main initial-drop-cap shares-position">
				
				
				<p>China’s condemnation of racism and police brutality in the United States looks hypocritical in comparison to its own human rights record.</p>
<p>Meanwhile, the strategic approach that led to China’s coronavirus response dates back further than President Xi Jinping’s rule.</p>
<p>And as businesses across the world begin the process of reopening after the pandemic, workers will be the group most vulnerable to another outbreak.</p>
<p>Here are <em>Foreign Policy</em>’s top weekend reads.</p>
<hr class="thick-horizontal-rule" />
<div id="attachment_1008857" class="wp-caption alignnone none text_width">            <span
                style="padding-bottom:66.625%;
        "
                class="image-attachment -ratioscale">
        <img
            data-srcset="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg 4926w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=550,367 550w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=2048,1365 2048w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=400,267 400w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=401,267 401w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=800,533 800w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=1920,1280 1920w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=275,183 275w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=325,217 325w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?resize=600,400 600w"
            data-src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?w=800"
            alt="White House Protesters"
            class="image alignnone size-text_width wp-image-1008857 -fit -lazy">
        <noscript>
            <img
                src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1217662332.jpg?w=800"
                alt="White House Protesters"
                class="image alignnone size-text_width wp-image-1008857 -fit">
        </noscript>
        </span>
        <p id="caption-attachment-1008857" class="wp-caption-text">People gather in the rain outside of the White House for a peaceful protest against police brutality in Washington on June 4. <span class="attribution">Sarah Silbiger/Getty Image</span> <!-- caption placeholder --></p></div>
<h4>1. <a href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/06/05/us-injustice-protests-china-condemnation-cynical/">As U.S. Injustices Rage, China’s Condemnation Reeks of Cynicism</a></h4>
<p>The Chinese Communist Party is condemning the United States for its record on police brutality and racism, but China’s own human rights record raises questions about its motivations, Ho-fung Hung writes.</p>
<hr class="thick-horizontal-rule" />
<div id="attachment_1008748" class="wp-caption alignnone none text_width">            <span
                style="padding-bottom:66.625%;
        "
                class="image-attachment -ratioscale">
        <img
            data-srcset="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg 1501w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=550,366 550w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=400,266 400w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=401,267 401w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=800,533 800w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=275,183 275w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=325,217 325w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?resize=600,400 600w"
            data-src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?w=800"
            alt="Chinese President Xi Jinping, right, shakes hands with China&#039;s former President Hu Jintao"
            class="image alignnone size-text_width wp-image-1008748 -fit -lazy">
        <noscript>
            <img
                src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-865658624.jpg?w=800"
                alt="Chinese President Xi Jinping, right, shakes hands with China&#039;s former President Hu Jintao"
                class="image alignnone size-text_width wp-image-1008748 -fit">
        </noscript>
        </span>
        <p id="caption-attachment-1008748" class="wp-caption-text">Chinese President Xi Jinping, right, shakes hands with former President Hu Jintao at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing on Oct. 24, 2017.<span class="attribution">Wang Zhao/AFP via Getty Images</span> <!-- caption placeholder --></p></div>
<h4>2. <a href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/06/04/china-xi-jingping-hu-jintao-aggression-ideology/">China’s Steps Backward Began Under Hu Jintao</a></h4>
<p>Xi’s predecessor presided over changes to the Chinese Communist Party’s internal system that set the stage for the reckless response to the coronavirus pandemic, Dan Blumenthal writes.</p>
<hr class="thick-horizontal-rule" />
<div id="attachment_1008140" class="wp-caption alignnone none text_width">            <span
                style="padding-bottom:66.625%;
        "
                class="image-attachment -ratioscale">
        <img
            data-srcset="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg 4096w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=550,367 550w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=2048,1365 2048w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=400,267 400w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=401,267 401w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=800,533 800w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=1920,1280 1920w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=275,183 275w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=325,217 325w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/GettyImages-1184173515.jpg?resize=600,400 600w"
